), in side view slightly bent forward (
<figureCitation box="[657,795,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 91–92</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[828,844,404,418]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">nd</superScript>
