<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="370" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,683]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,303,549,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Remark.</emphasis>
In the shape of genitalia fits the description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[838,1041,549,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori (1978)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[1058,1195,549,576]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 63–67</figureCitation>
). Dark coloured male (
<figureCitation box="[159,291,585,612]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 16–18</figureCitation>
) in external appearance is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1978" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[704,1052,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bitaeniata">
<emphasis box="[704,852,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">M. bitaeniata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[860,1052,585,611]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
known by the only male from 
<collectingCountry name="Yemen" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Yemen</collectingCountry>
, but differs from it by somewhat more narrow penis and narrower style tip (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1158,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figs. 80–81</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1211,1284,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–117" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1860,1885]" captionTargetBox="[246,1350,176,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[236,1352,166,1840]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 82–117. 82–94—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori; 95–108—M. nikippa Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 109–117—M. antibia Tisheсhkin sp. n. 82–83, 95–96—male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 84–85, 97–98―the 2nd sternite; 86–87, 99–100, 110—penis, lateral view; 88–89, 101–102, 113—style; 90—pygofer processes, back view; 91–92, 103–104, 111—pygofer process, lateral view; 105, 112—pygofer process, dorsolateral view; 93, 106–107, 114–115—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 94, 108, 116–117—female 7th sternite; 109—male 2nd abdominal apodemes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772395/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">86–89</figureCitation>
). Possibly, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bitaeniata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">M. bitaeniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[315,494,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippodameia">
<emphasis box="[315,494,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">M. hippodameia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are conspecific, but more material is needed for elucidation their taxonomic status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
